101.subject: ARAB
101.courseDescription: (ARAB 1411, 1511) Beginning Arabic I. (4-0). Credit 4. Introduction to Modern Standard Arabic in its written and spoken forms; emphasis on conversation, rudimentary vocabulary, simple grammar, and reading.

102.subject: ARAB
102.courseDescription: (ARAB 1412, 1512) Beginning Arabic II. (4-0). Credit 4. Introduction of more complex grammatical constructions; vocabulary building; emphasis on putting acquired vocabulary and grammar to conversational use. Prerequisite: ARAB 101 or equivalent.

201.subject: ARAB
201.courseDescription: (ARAB 2311) Intermediate Arabic I. (3-0). Credit 3. Practice of listening, speaking, and writing skills; vocabulary building; discussion of topics related to daily life and general aspects of Arab culture. Prerequisite: ARAB 102 or equivalent.

202.subject: ARAB
202.courseDescription: (ARAB 2312) Intermediate Arabic II. (3-0). Credit 3. Emphasis on comprehending printed material, perfecting pronunciation, and attending to more complex grammar; discussion of topics holding general and professional interest; knowledge of Arab culture and history. Prerequisite: ARAB 201 or equivalent.

221.subject: ARAB
221.courseDescription: Introduction to Arabic Language and Society. (3-0). Credit 3. Examination of critical linguistic issues in the Arab world from a sociolinguistic perspective, including language and religion; language and power; language and nationalism; and language and education. Prerequisite: Approval of instructor.

222.subject: ARAB
222.courseDescription: Field Studies I: Language, Culture, and Society. (3-0). Credit 3. Arabic language and culture taught in an Arabic-speaking country; living with a host family; supervised travel of cultural interest; participation in activities of host institution. Prerequisite: ARAB 102 or equivalent.

285.subject: ARAB
285.courseDescription: Directed Studies.  Credit 1 to 4. Individual supervision of readings or assigned projects in an Asian Language, selected for each student individually; written or oral reports. Prerequisite: Approval of Arabic and Asian Language Office Director.

289.subject: ARAB
289.courseDescription: Special Topics in...  Credit 1 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of Arabic studies. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisite: Approval of instructor.

301.subject: ARAB
301.courseDescription: Reading and Composition. (3-0). Credit 3. Advanced Arabic grammar and readings of average difficulty and of different genres, including literary and journalistic texts and other culturally-enriched materials in order to develop awareness of cultural products, perspectives, and practices found in the Arab world. Prerequisites: ARAB 202; junior or senior classification or approval of instructor.

302.subject: ARAB
302.courseDescription: Reading and Composition II. (3-0). Credit 3. Readings of average difficulty and of different genres, including literary and journalistic texts and other culturally-enriched materials; development of writing skills with emphasis on grammatical constructions; expansion of vocabulary and oral expression. Prerequisites: ARAB 301; junior or senior classification or approval of instructor.

322.subject: ARAB
322.courseDescription: Field Studies II: Language, Culture, and Society. (3-0). Credit 3. Arabic language and culture taught in an Arabic-speaking country; living with a host family; supervised travel of cultural interest; participation in activities of host institution. Prerequisite: ARAB 202 or equivalent.

485.subject: ARAB
485.courseDescription: Directed Studies.  Credit 1 to 4. Individual supervision of readings or assigned projects selected for each student individually; written or oral reports. Prerequisite: Approval of instructor and Director of AALO.

489.subject: ARAB
489.courseDescription: Special Topics in...  Credit 1 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of Arabic studies. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisite: Approval of instructor.

491.subject: ARAB
491.courseDescription: Research. Credit 1 to 4. Research in Arabic studies conducted under the direction of faculty member approved by the Director of AALO. May be taken 2 times for credit. Prerequisites: Junior or senior classification and approval of instructor.
